HOUSE BILL 16
E5 6lr0856
HB 1156/25 – JUD (PRE–FILED)
By: Delegate Phillips Delegates Phillips, Simmons, Moreno, Moon, Conaway, and
Williams
Requested: September 16, 2025
Introduced and read first time: January 14, 2026
Assigned to: Judiciary
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted with floor amendments
Read second time: March 9, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Correctional Services – Maryland Parole Commission – Members and Hearing
3 Examiners
4 FOR the purpose of altering the number of members of the Maryland Parole Commission;
5 altering the appointing authority and method of appointment of parole
6 commissioners; repealing the authority of the Commission to appoint and utilize
7 hearing examiners; requiring a new commissioner to be appointed within a certain
8 number of days under certain circumstances; prohibiting a hearing examiner
9 appointed under certain authority from serving for more than a certain number of
10 days; altering certain requirements for hearing examiners; requiring a vote of the
11 majority of commissioners appointed to the Maryland Parole Commission, instead of
12 a certain minimum number, to approve a certain incarcerated individual for parole;
13 and generally relating to the Maryland Parole Commission.
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
15 Article – Correctional Services
16 Section 7–202, 7–204, 7–205(a), and 7–307, 7–207, 7–302, 7–303, and 7–305
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2025 Replacement Volume)
19 BY repealing
20 Article – Correctional Services
21 Section 7–306
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
