16 (3) A hearing examiner appointed under this subsection is entitled to the
17 same compensation as a commissioner.
18 (3) (4) A hearing examiner appointed under this subsection may not:
19 (I) SERVE FOR MORE THAN 90 DAYS; OR
20 (II) participate in a proceeding before the Commission in which the
21 hearing examiner participated as a hearing examiner.
22 (g)] With the approval of the Governor, the Secretary shall designate a
23 chairperson of the Commission from among its members.
