29 (2) negotiate, enter into, and sign predetermined parole release
30 agreements as provided under subsection (b) of this section;
31 (3) hear cases for parole or administrative release [in which:

6 HOUSE BILL 16
1 (i) the Commissioner of Correction, after reviewing the
2 recommendation of the appropriate managing official, objects to a parole;
